For anyone using an LG V20, go into the phone's "game battery saver" and turn it on, then go into "optimization by game" and set the resolution for NES.Emu to "normal." After that, open the app and set the frame rate to detect whatever your screen is. Set the skip late frames to "On." Set GPU Copy Mode to "standard." If you're using a Bluetooth controller, turn off mobile data and Wi-Fi or else you'll get input delay. Enjoy!
